 *Protect a Branch on GitHub*
To protect a branch on GitHub:

Go to your repository on GitHub.
Click on the Settings tab.
In the left sidebar, click Branches.
Under the "Branch protection rules" section, click Add rule.
In the "Branch name pattern" field, specify the branch you want to protect (e.g., main, develop).

 *To remove protection from a branch:*

Go to your repository on GitHub.
Click on the Settings tab.
In the left sidebar, click Branches.
Under "Branch protection rules," find the rule associated with the branch you want to unlock.
Click the Delete button next to the branch protection rule.
Confirm the deletion of the rule.



  **Cloning one branch from github**

git clone --branch <branch-name> --single-branch <repository-url>



push Issue:



# Fetch the latest changes from the remote repository
git fetch origin

# Merge or rebase
git merge origin/Tasks  # OR git rebase origin/Tasks

# Resolve conflicts if necessary, then stage the changes
git add <file_with_conflicts>
git commit  # Only for merge

# If rebasing, continue rebasing
git rebase --continue  # Only for rebase

# Finally, push your changes
git push origin Tasks


